---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { buildHolidayWebPageSchema } from '../../lib/seo';

const title = 'NZ Public Holidays 2026 | Complete Calendar New Zealand';
const description = 'How mondayisation works for New Zealand public holidays, including NZ holidays 2026 transfer rules for Waitangi Day and Anzac Day.';
const pageSchema = buildHolidayWebPageSchema('/guide/how-mondayisation-works-nz', title, description);
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/guide/how-mondayisation-works-nz" jsonLd={pageSchema}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-black">How mondayisation works in NZ</h1>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground">
      Mondayisation is the public holiday transfer rule in New Zealand. If certain holidays fall on Saturday or Sunday,
      eligible employees can observe the holiday on Monday (or Tuesday for New Year sequence cases).
    </p>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Which holidays can be transferred?</h2>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground">Waitangi Day and Anzac Day are mondayised when they fall on weekends. New Year and Christmas-related holidays also have transfer mechanics.</p>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Who receives the mondayised day?</h2>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground">Eligibility depends on whether the holiday is an otherwise working day for the employee. Employment agreements and payroll settings matter.</p>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Why it matters</h2>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground">Mondayisation affects leave planning, staffing, and payroll compliance. Check your region and contract terms before scheduling shifts.</p>
    <p class="text-sm">Back to the <a href="/guide" class="font-bold text-primary hover:underline underline-offset-4">holiday guide</a>.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>
